    <b><i>Hi Sandra, <br /><br />
    We have a good size walk out basement that we would like to design for several functions but want it to feature a new large screen TV.  The space has neutral carpet and paint and recessed lights equipped with dimmers. How can we make it cozy and welcoming?
    <br /><br />
    Jayne L. - Martinsville, NJ </i></b>
    <br /><br />
    Having your room be multi-purpose, is a good way to make the most of the space.  The traditional separate media rooms are designed with a host of specialty features such as light and sound controls, and of course the movie theater row style seating.  While this is a very luxurious feature in a home, it may not be right for everyone due to space or budget constraints.
